{
  "topicId": "m5-t1",
  "title": "Asking About the Location of Things (وين؟)",
  "dialect": "levantine",
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Introducing 'Where?' (وين؟)"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'Where?' in Levantine Arabic, we use the word 'وين؟'. This is a fundamental question word when inquiring about location.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "وين؟",
            "english": "Where?",
            "transliteration": "Wayn?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "وين؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Common Objects: Book and Pen"
        },
        "text": "Let's learn some common objects to ask about their location. Today we start with 'book' and 'pen'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كتاب",
            "english": "Book",
            "transliteration": "ktaab"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "قلم",
            "english": "Pen",
            "transliteration": "qalam"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "كتاب، قلم"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Where is the...?'"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'Where is the [object]?', you simply combine 'وين؟' with the object. The definite article 'الـ' (al-) for 'the' is implicitly understood or attached to the object.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "وين الكتاب؟",
            "english": "Where is the book?",
            "transliteration": "Wayn el-ktaab?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "وين القلم؟",
            "english": "Where is the pen?",
            "transliteration": "Wayn el-qalam?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "وين الكتاب؟ وين القلم؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "وين قَلَمي؟",
        "english": "Where is my pen?",
        "transliteration": "Wayn qalami?"
      },
      "context": "Asking about a personal item."
    },
    {
      "type": "practice-sentence",
      "sentence": {
        "arabic": "وين كتابك؟",
        "english": "Where is your book? (masculine)",
        "transliteration": "Wayn ktaabak?"
      },
      "context": "Asking about someone else's item."
    },
    {
