    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition: 'On' / 'Upon' (على)"
        },
        "text": "The preposition 'على' is used to say 'on' or 'upon'. It indicates that something is resting directly on a surface.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "على",
            "english": "On / Upon",
            "transliteration": "3ala"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "على"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition: 'In' / 'At' (في)"
        },
        "text": "The preposition 'في' is used to say 'in' or 'at'. It indicates that something is inside or located at a general place.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "في",
            "english": "In / At",
            "transliteration": "fi"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "في"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition: 'Under' (تحت)"
        },
        "text": "The preposition 'تحت' is used to say 'under' or 'below'. It indicates that something is situated beneath another object.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "تحت",
            "english": "Under",
            "transliteration": "taḥt"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "تحت"
      }
    },
