    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition: 'Next to' / 'Beside' (جنب)"
        },
        "text": "To describe something as being 'next to' or 'beside' another object, use the word 'جنب'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "جنب",
            "english": "Next to / Beside",
            "transliteration": "janb"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "جنب"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition: 'Above' / 'Over' (فوق)"
        },
        "text": "The word 'فوق' means 'above' or 'over'. It suggests a position higher than something else, but not necessarily touching it (unlike 'على').",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "فوق",
            "english": "Above / Over",
            "transliteration": "fawq"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "فوق"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Preposition: 'In front of' (قدّام)"
        },
        "text": "To say 'in front of', use 'قدّام'. This preposition describes a position facing or ahead of another object.",
        "examples": [
